sentences: Boubacar Traoré (born 1942 in Kayes, Mali) is a Malian singer, songwriter, and guitarist.
In 1968, when Moussa Traoré overthrew Malian president Modibo Keïta, Boubacar Traoré, widely seen as an artist associated with the previous regime, disappeared from the airwaves.
During the 1970s Traoré's popularity faded, until a surprise television appearance in 1987.
